attributionInfo.brokerName: Better Homes and Gardens Real Estate Welcome Home

data.description: Check out this beautiful 4 bedroom 3 bath custom built 3893 sq. ft. home on 6.33 acres with detached 3 bay garage/shop, owned solar, pool with waterfall, paved circle driveway, views of the beautiful foothills and so much more! This spacious home feels even bigger and brighter with its vaulted ceilings and skylights that allow a ton of natural light. The kitchen features granite countertops, maple cabinets, double ovens and many extras! Multiple entertaining areas, including a secondary living room/bonus room (currently being used as 4th bedroom), makes this a great space to be with family and friends. Spacious master suite has a walk-in closet, dedicated fireplace and direct access to the back deck. Many unique extras throughout the home. Water is everything and this house has it all! Approximately 10gpm well feeds 5000 gallons of holding tanks. Booster pump and pressure tank supply house and pool with this fresh drinking water. Well, booster pump, and pressure tank all recently replaced and under warranty. Piped, pressurized, and filtered irrigation water from South Feather Water and Power supplies the rest of property through numerous sprinklers and hose connections. 30,000 to 40,000 gallons of water per day supplied to property through this 1 inch line. Power is everything else and this property delivers 400 amps of service.  200 amps residential and 200 amps Ag power, which is much cheaper. House has a selector switch to run on either.  Solar panels and a windmill top it all off. Property has been fenced and cross fenced, and has numerous buildings, including an area with horse barn and pasture, 1000 sq ft shipping container barn, small "doll house" building (currently being used for beauty business), and 2 RV hook-ups with separate entrance. Both RV spots have 50 amps of Ag power with pressurized drinking water. Easy access to property on roads that are dust stabilized and maintained by the County and behave like asphalt. The possibilities are endless with this property and could be the perfect forever home. Schedule an appointment before it's gone.
